      "question": "Assertion (A): For any two positive integers $a$ and $b$, if $HCF(a, b) = 11$ and $LCM(a, b) = 693$, then the product $a \\times b = 7623$. Reason (R): For any two positive integers $a$ and $b$, $HCF(a, b) \\times LCM(a, b) = a \\times b$.",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the relationship between HCF, LCM and the product of two numbers.",
          "Check the assertion: $11 \\times 693 = 7623$.",
          "Verify the Reason: The property $HCF(a, b) \\times LCM(a, b) = a \\times b$ is a standard theorem for positive integers.",
          "Conclude that both are true and the reason explains the assertion."
        ],
        "derivation": "$11 \\times 693 = 7623 \\\\ \\text{Since } HCF(a, b) \\times LCM(a, b) = a \\times b \\text{ is always true, the assertion follows from the reason.}"
